# M15b canary per GPT-5.5 post-impl review: the M22.1 anonymous-
# resource-temp rule must fire for cross-module resource-returning
# calls. `a.make_box()` returns `*Box`; using `.value` on it
# anonymously would leak the Rc the same way `(*Box(...)).value`
# does (no M20e auto-drop guard, since guards key off named
# bindings). The type-aware tier of `isResourceOwningType`
# inspects the imported function's return type and fires.
use a

sub main()
  print(a.make_box().value)
